   </title>
   <section id="import-auto-id1167819595690">
    <title>
Organs and tissues
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id1167819661550">
An
     <emphasis effect="bold">
organ
     </emphasis>
is a collection of
     <link url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tissue_(biology)">
tissues
     </link>
joined in structural unit to serve a common function. Functionally related
organs often cooperate to form whole
     <link target-id="">
organ systems
     </link>
. Organs exist in all higher biological organisms, they are not restricted to
animals, but can also be identified in plants, e.g. the leaf is an organ in a
plant as is the root, stem, flowers and fruits.
    </para>
