   <section id="import-auto-id1167819648178">
    <title>
Leaf Structure
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id1167819532370">
The leaf is the main photosynthesising organ of a plant. The Leaf is an organ
because it contains a number of tissues including epidermis, xylem, phloem and
parenchyma working together to make food for the plant in photosynthesis.
    </para>
    
    <para id="eip-725"><figure id="import-auto-id1167819667001"><media id="import-auto-id1167819677644" alt="">
